REFERENCE CONCEPT I LOVE:
I have seen a contact form where the HTML form inputs (name, email, checkbox, submit) are overlaid on a large SVG canvas. The SVG contains animated mechanical machines — gears, pulleys, a spray hand, a grabbing hand, scales, a car, timing chains, spiral springs, weight objects — all connected together. As the user interacts with the form fields, the machines react:
- Typing a valid name → gears start spinning, which drives a piston, which powers a spray gun that slowly paints the submit button visible
- Typing a valid email → a spiral spring winds up, a hammer strikes, a grabbing hand closes, a car launches on a ramp
- Checking a checkbox → a pulley system pulls a rope that rotates the submit button into place
- All conditions met + submit clicked → all SVG elements fade out randomly with staggered opacity

The key idea: the form fields are invisible inputs floating over a large SVG mechanical illustration. Filling the form DRIVES the machines. The machines are the visual feedback. GSAP handles all animation. The SVG is pointer-events:none so inputs work normally underneath.

YOUR TASK:
Create a completely new version of this concept adapted to my theme. Same core idea — HTML form inputs overlaid on a large SVG canvas with interconnected animated machines that react to form interaction — but completely redesigned to match my dark sci-fi space theme.

