Complete Prompt
"Create a single HTML file — a portfolio hero intro animation for a developer named "Saadany". Here is every detail:

The Scene

Background: solid off-white/cream #faf9f7
A thin vertical bar (5px wide, full height) on the far left edge of the screen, gradient from pale lavender at top to deep lavender #9b7cc8 at bottom — purely decorative accent
A subtle grain/noise texture overlay on the entire page at very low opacity (~2%)
Custom cursor: a small 7px filled dark circle that replaces the default cursor


The Word "Saadany"

Font: Cormorant Garamond, weight 300, very large — around clamp(64px, 11vw, 150px)
Color: dark ink #1c1a22
Positioned at the horizontal and vertical center of the screen as its final resting place
Starts off-screen to the LEFT before the animation begins
Each letter is wrapped in its own <span class="ch"> so they can be animated individually
On arrival, each letter bounces down into place one by one with a staggered bounce.out ease (left to right, 0.038s between each letter) — like the letters are raining down and landing


The Character — THIS IS THE MOST IMPORTANT PART
The character is drawn entirely with Canvas 2D API (NOT SVG, NOT divs). It is drawn every frame inside a requestAnimationFrame loop on a full-screen fixed canvas that sits on top of everything.
The character has these exact body parts, all drawn with canvas arc/bezier/rect calls:
Head:

A perfect circle, filled with a warm cream-to-beige vertical gradient (#f8f3ec → #e8d9c4), dark outline 2.2px
Two eyes: white filled circles with dark outlines, pupils that can shift position (used for looking in different directions)
Each pupil has a small white specular dot (shine) in the upper-left
Eyebrows: two short angled lines above the eyes — angle changes based on emotion
Mouth: changes shape based on state — smile arc when happy, flat horizontal line when determined/pushing, wide open ellipse when shocked

Body:

A rounded rectangle (like a pill/capsule shape) below the head, same warm gradient fill, dark outline
A small soft ellipse on the belly area filled with semi-transparent white (highlight)
Connected directly to the head — NO gap between head bottom and body top

Arms:

Two lines extending from the sides of the body, one from upper-body left side, one from lower-body left side
Each arm ends in a small filled circle (the hand/fist)
Arm angle changes completely depending on animation state:

Running state: arms swing forward and back in opposite phase to legs (counter-swing like real running)
Push/windup state: both arms pulled BACK behind the body (telegraph)
Impact state: both arms THRUST fully forward to the right, hands pressing against the S
Celebrate state: both arms raised high, waving with a sine wave motion
Idle state: arms hang loosely at sides with a gentle sway



Legs:

Two lines extending from the BOTTOM CENTER of the body rectangle — hip joints at bottom-left and bottom-right of body, NOT floating below it
Each leg bends at a midpoint (quadratic bezier curve, not straight line) to simulate a knee
Each leg ends in a small horizontal ellipse (the foot/shoe), filled cream, dark outline
Running animation: legs swing forward and back using Math.sin(runPhase + offset) where offset = PI for the opposite leg, creating alternating stride. The knee bend exaggerates on the forward swing. Feet lift off the ground on the forward swing
The stride amplitude is large enough to clearly read as running

Squash and Stretch:

The character has sqX and sqY spring variables that smoothly lerp toward target values
Running: slightly tall and narrow (sqY = 1.1, sqX = 0.87)
Impact: very wide and short (sqX = 1.55, sqY = 0.62) — extreme horizontal squash
Jumping up: tall and narrow (sqY = 1.3, sqX = 0.82)
Landing: wide and short (sqY = 0.82, sqX = 1.2)
All squash values lerp at rate 0.18 per frame for springy feel

Lean:

A single rotation applied via ctx.rotate(lean) before drawing
Running: leans forward (-0.15 radians)
Windup: leans back (+0.22 radians) — like coiling before a punch
Impact: snaps forward lean (-0.18 radians)
Idle: gentle sine wave lean (very subtle, ±0.04 radians)

Sweat drop:

A small teardrop shape drawn above and to the right of the head
Appears with increasing opacity when the character is in windup or impact state
Filled with light blue #a8d8ea, thin blue outline

Speed lines:

3 horizontal lines of different lengths drawn to the RIGHT of the body when running
Semi-transparent lavender color
Sell the sense of speed

Ground shadow:

A soft semi-transparent ellipse drawn below the feet
Scales slightly with squash state


Animation States (State Machine)
The character runs through these states in order:
1. STATE: RUN

Character moves rightward across the screen at 7.5px per frame
Full leg stride animation, arms counter-swinging, speed lines visible
Leans forward, slightly squashed tall
Dust puff particles spawn behind the feet every 5 frames (small lavender circles that fade out)
Transitions to WINDUP when character X reaches the push target position

2. STATE: WINDUP (18 frames)

Character stops moving horizontally
Leans BACK (coiling)
Arms pulled behind body
Wide squat squash (sqX = 1.26, sqY = 0.78)
Sweat drop appears
After 18 frames: triggers the word animation AND transitions to IMPACT
This is the telegraph — the player/viewer knows something is about to happen

3. STATE: IMPACT (14 frames)

Arms THRUST forward
Extreme horizontal squash (sqX = 1.55, sqY = 0.62)
Burst particles explode outward (mix of circles and 5-pointed stars, lavender and deep lavender colors)
Transitions to IDLE after 14 frames

4. STATE: CELEBRATE (75 frames)

Character jumps up (jumpVy = -14, gravity = +0.78 per frame)
